&lt;h2&gt;1. The Core Philosophy&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MindLeap is built on the &lt;b&gt;Spaced Repetition System (SRS)&lt;/b&gt;. Instead of cramming all at once, you review information at increasing intervals. This exploits the &quot;spacing effect&quot; to move knowledge from short-term to long-term memory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;2. Getting Started&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Creating Decks&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start by creating a &lt;b&gt;Deck&lt;/b&gt; for each subject you want to learn (e.g., &quot;Spanish Vocabulary&quot;, &quot;Organic Chemistry&quot;). Decks keep your study material organized and allow you to focus on one topic at a time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Adding Cards&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inside a deck, click &lt;b&gt;Add Card&lt;/b&gt;. Keep your cards simple: one question and one clear answer. If a concept is complex, break it into multiple smaller cards.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;3. The Study Process&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you open a deck, you'll see cards that are &lt;b&gt;Due&lt;/b&gt; for review. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Recall:&lt;/b&gt; Look at the question and try to remember the answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Show Answer:&lt;/b&gt; Click the button to reveal the back of the card.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Rate Yourself:&lt;/b&gt; This is the most important step! Be honest.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Rating Buttons Explained&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Again:&lt;/b&gt; You didn't remember it. The card stays in the &quot;Learning&quot; phase and will reappear in a few minutes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Hard:&lt;/b&gt; You remembered it, but with great effort. The next review will be soon.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Good:&lt;/b&gt; You remembered it after a short thought. This is the ideal rating for most cards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Easy:&lt;/b&gt; You knew the answer instantly. The card will disappear for a long time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;4. Advanced Features&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Statistics Tracking&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check the &lt;b&gt;Stats&lt;/b&gt; menu to see your progress. MindLeap tracks your accuracy, how many cards you've added, and how much time you've spent studying. Watching these numbers grow is a great way to stay motivated!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Personalized Settings&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use the &lt;b&gt;Preferences&lt;/b&gt; to adjust daily card limits. Don't set these too highâ€”consistency is better than volume.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;5. Pro Tips for Success&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Daily Habit:&lt;/b&gt; Spaced repetition only works if you do your reviews every day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Simple Cards:&lt;/b&gt; The shorter the card, the easier it is to remember.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Context:&lt;/b&gt; If you're learning language, try to include a short example sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
